.TH "_dpu_plane_calc_bw" 9 "_dpu_plane_calc_bw" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_dpu_plane_calc_bw \- calculate bandwidth required for a plane
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" _dpu_plane_calc_bw
.BI "(struct drm_plane *plane "  ","
.BI "struct drm_framebuffer *fb "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "plane" 12
Pointer to drm plane.
.IP "fb" 12
Pointer to framebuffer associated with the given plane
Result: Updates calculated bandwidth in the plane state.
BW Equation: src_w * src_h * bpp * fps * (v_total / v_dest)
Prefill BW Equation: line src bytes * line_time
